    <p>
        Foreigners Visiting Darjeeling Must Possess An Indian Visa. No Special Permits Is Required For Those Coming To Darjeeling
        For Indian Nationals No Such Permits Are Required At All, However It Is Mandatory To Carry Any Of The Indian Identification Documents For Safety And Incase If Opt For Sikkim Trekking Trip Later During The Trip.
    </p>
    <p>
        For Trekking Advance Information With Relevant Documents Copies Of Valid Passport, Visa & Photos Is Required.
    </p>
    <p class="text-info">
        Nationals From Pakistan, China, Myanmar, Bangladesh, Afghanistan, Ghana, Iraq, Palestine, Nigeria, Swaziland, Cameroon, Ethiopia, Liberia, Somalia And Zimbabwe Need To Obtain The Prior Approval Of The Ministry Of Home Affairs, Government Of India, New Delhi To Visit.
    </p>
